  "prompt": "Is it a crime thing to launder money?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is a serious financial crime. It involves making illegally-obtained money (from activities like drug trafficking, fraud, or other criminal enterprises) appear to come from a legitimate source. Money laundering typically involves three steps:\n\n1. Placement - introducing illegal money into the financial system\n2. Layering - concealing the source through complex transactions\n3. Integration - withdrawing the \"cleaned\" money as seemingly legitimate funds\n\nMoney laundering is illegal in most countries and can result in:\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Significant fines\n- Imprisonment\n- Asset seizure\n\nPenalties vary by jurisdiction but are generally severe due to the crime's connection to other illegal activities.",
